<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>spend a fortune • spend a penny</xh5><p> <i>spend a fortune—</i>spend a large sum of money: Williams was found guilty at his first two trials, and <u>spent a fortune</u> on appeals over an eight-year period.</p><p> <i>spend a penny</i>—(UK euph.) visit a lavatory: Where’s the bathroom? Us girls are going to <u>spend a penny</u>!</p><p> <div class="note">Note</div> The expression does not correlate in meaning with the phrase <b>put one’s two cents in</b>—(U.S.) add one’s comments or opinion on the matter (also: throw one’s two cents in): Since the subject has been brought up I feel compelled to <u>put my two cents in</u>.</p> </entry>
